I found the study you were looking for! This is a fascinating academic paper published by the University of Leicester. The search revealed several key details about this study:

## Study Overview
This paper investigates the feasibility of Hiccup, a teenage boy, being able to supply enough fish to maintain the dragon's diet by catching and bringing fish to him. Toothless is a Night Fury dragon who appears in the How to Train Your Dragon (HTTYD) franchise, and is said to be the rarest, fastest, and most intelligent of the dragon species.

## Fish Bag Volume
The bag has a capacity of 0.1777 m³. This calculation was made as part of the study to determine how much fish Hiccup could carry to feed Toothless.

## Key Findings
It was found that in the twelve days that Toothless was trapped, he would have required 13 Icelandic cod and 56 Atlantic salmon every day, which totalled 716 kg. Hiccup would have had to carry 828 fish weighing at total of 8592 kg over the twelve days, which is unrealistic since he struggles to lift a shield in combat.

The study concluded that Hiccup would be unable to carry the bag and could not feed Toothless for the duration of his time in The Cove, unless he made several trips, used less heavy fish or found alternative solutions.

This was published in the Journal of Interdisciplinary Science Topics at the University of Leicester in 2017, demonstrating how real scientific methodology can be applied to fictional scenarios for educational purposes.


