Based on the search results, I found information about dinosaur-related Wikipedia Featured Articles promoted in November 2016. Here's what I discovered:

The Giganotosaurus article was promoted to Featured Article status on November 19, 2016 by Ian Rose via FACBot. This article is about one of the largest known meat-eating dinosaurs, and therefore one of the largest terrestrial carnivores to have ever existed.

Additionally, while not promoted in November 2016 but nominated that month, the Paranthodon article was nominated on November 27, 2016 and later promoted to Featured Article status on January 13, 2017. This article is about the dinosaur genus Paranthodon, arguably one of the most obscure dinosaurs, with the only bone known being part of a skull.

The search results also show that there was active discussion and review of these dinosaur articles during November 2016, with various editors including FunkMonk (a prolific dinosaur article contributor) working on improving and reviewing these articles for Featured Article status.


